# Pairs trading in six lines. spread($GLD, $GDX) is the ratio of gold
# to gold miners — it behaves exactly like price, so every comparison
# works on it. Buying the spread means long GLD / short GDX in equal
# dollar legs (market exposure ~0); the trade is the RELATIONSHIP
# reverting, not either ticker going up.

strategy "Gold Miners Ratio"

when spread($GLD, $GDX) at [lower_bollinger 60]
  buy [10% portfolio]

sell when spread($GLD, $GDX) at [middle_bollinger 60]
  or [after 40 bars]
